- 'First factor' refers to the factor with the ID of 0;
- 'Significant market risk premium' refers to an average market risk premium greater than 0.02.

- "Blooming portfolios" refers to the top 3 performing portfolios based on average returns;
- "Nourish them" refers to the factors to which the portfolios have exposure;
- "Nourishment level (exposure) is more than half" means the total exposure to the factor is greater than 0.5.
